<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="request-n">request <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'kwest/    美 /rɪ'kwest/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>（正式的）要求；请求：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>make</strong> a <strong>request for</strong> help
请求帮助</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In Japan, the “OK” sign is a <strong>request for</strong> small change. 
在日本，手势OK表示要零钱。</p><footer>译林⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pianist listened to our <strong>request that</strong> he (should) play in public again. 
那位钢琴家听从了我们的请求，答应再次公演。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="at-sbs-request-at-the-request-of-sb">at sb’s request / at the request of sb</h3>
<p>1.<strong>应某人的要求：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The students were there at the teacher’s request. 
学生们应老师的要求到了那里。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>We most prefer to say yes to the <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ of someone we know and like.  （2014 浙江）<br />
A.attempts<br />
B.requests<br />
C.doubts<br />
D.promises  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. B  </p></div>